Branching Statements:
- used for branchings
- 3 branching statements:
    1. break:
        - used to terminate execution of a loop or switch and to continue to next statement
            while (condition){statem1; statem2; break; statem3; statem4;}statem5;
            ==>break statement jumps out of loop -> stops after statem2 and continues with statem5

    2. continue:
        - used to skip remaining code inside a loop iteration and move to next iteration
          -> jumps to next iteration of loop , remaining iteration of loop will not be executed
          for(initialization; condition; iterator){
          st1;
          st2;
          continue;
          st3;
          st4;
          }
          st5;
          ==> st3 & st4 will be skipped for specific iteration, but next iteration they will be executed


    3. return:
        - exits a method and can return a value
        example:
        main{
        st1;
        st2;
        return;
        st3;
        st4;
      }
      -> current method will be terminated
      example 2:
       main{
       do{
              st1;
              st2;
              return;
              st3;
              st4;
            } while (condition);
            st5;
            }
    -> inside loop also terminates method
    -> next code fragments in codes body will never be executed





